1.title: Episode #1.1

episode of.title: High School King of Savvy (TV Series 2014– )

1.plot: Popular high schooler Lee Min Seok waits for his lookalike brother to come home, while temp worker Jung Soo Young develops a crush on Yoo Jin Woo, a stoic director within her company.

2.title: Episode #1.2

episode of.title: High School King of Savvy (TV Series 2014– )

2.plot: Min Seok begins his double life as a student and posing as his older brother at Comfo, but he doesn't have a clue about what to actually do.

3.title: Episode #1.3

episode of.title: High School King of Savvy (TV Series 2014– )

3.plot: Min Seok starts to get the hang of his role at Comfo. His favorite part? Torturing Soo Young about her one-sided crush on Jin Woo.

4.title: Episode #1.4

episode of.title: High School King of Savvy (TV Series 2014– )

4.plot: Min Seok's best friends learn about his double life, and they want to reap the benefits too. A competitor causes trouble for Comfo, and Jin Woo must catch the sneaky employee behind it.

5.title: Episode #1.5

episode of.title: High School King of Savvy (TV Series 2014– )

5.plot: Soo Young learns that her contract at Comfo has not been renewed, which puts Min Seok and Jin Woo at odds.

6.title: Episode #1.6

episode of.title: High School King of Savvy (TV Series 2014– )

6.plot: Min Seok offers Soo Young a job as his secretary after she's fired from the company. Jin Woo is suspicious of Min Seok and reaches out to Soo Young.

7.title: Episode #1.7

episode of.title: High School King of Savvy (TV Series 2014– )

7.plot: The Comfo employees go on a trip together. Jin Woo continues to get closer to Soo Young, provoking Min Seok's jealousy.

8.title: Episode #1.8

episode of.title: High School King of Savvy (TV Series 2014– )

8.plot: Min Seok confesses his feelings to Soo Young, but she is hesitant to reciprocate after having her heart broken by Jin Woo.

9.title: Episode #1.9

episode of.title: High School King of Savvy (TV Series 2014– )

9.plot: Min Seok and Soo Young are giddy about their new relationship, but must keep it a secret around their co-workers.

10.title: Episode #1.10

episode of.title: High School King of Savvy (TV Series 2014– )

10.plot: Jin Woo inches closer to finding out Min Seok's secret, and the rivalry between the two heats up. Min Seok begins to feel guilty about hiding his identity from Soo Young.

11.title: Episode #1.11

episode of.title: High School King of Savvy (TV Series 2014– )

11.plot: When Soo Young discovers Min Seok's real age and identity, her relationship with him, as well as with Yoo Ah, begins to crumble.

12.title: Episode #1.12

episode of.title: High School King of Savvy (TV Series 2014– )

12.plot: Soo Young does her best to keep her relationship with Min Seok purely platonic. Min Seok has a life-changing accident.

13.title: Episode #1.13

episode of.title: High School King of Savvy (TV Series 2014– )

13.plot: After getting back together, Soo Young helps Min Seok manage his hectic double life. Jin Woo learns about the secret past between his father and Min Seok's.

14.title: Episode #1.14

episode of.title: High School King of Savvy (TV Series 2014– )

14.plot: Jin Woo toys with Min Seok, threatening to reveal his identity to the entire company, but Jin Woo's own secrets begin to take a toll on him.

15.title: Episode #1.15

episode of.title: High School King of Savvy (TV Series 2014– )

15.plot: Hyung Seok returns, but Min Seok's excitement dwindles quickly when he finds out what his brother has really been up to.

16.title: Episode #1.16

episode of.title: High School King of Savvy (TV Series 2014– )

16.plot: After his grandfather's untimely death, Hyung Seok must decide whether or not to follow through with his revenge.

17.title: Episode #1.17

episode of.title: High School King of Savvy (TV Series 2014– )

17.plot: Min Seok and Soo Young decide the only way to stay together is to get married, but first, they must convince their family and friends.

imdb.title: High School King of Savvy
plot: Can a high school boy lead a double life? Lee Min Seok (Seo In Guk) is a rising hockey player at his high school leading an average high school life, complete with a groupie classmate, Jung Yoo Ah (Lee Yeol Eum), who has a crush on him.
